text.tspan: Allows for precise adjustment to compensate for uneven or non-plumb concrete block walls,
ensuring tiles remain parallel and perpendicular to the ground.
Handmade, vitrified high-fire clay prevents freeze-thaw damage.
Inner clay ribs maintain structural integrity during drying and firing.
The tiles have an open back to accommodate assembly and anchoring hardware.
Extruded aluminum channels transfer the weight of the cantilevered tiles
onto the concrete block structural wall.
An aluminum angle that distributes the tile’s weight onto the metal frame.
Adjustable for a plumb and parallel tile mounting surface,
compensating for an uneven or non-plumb concrete block wall.
It features vertical slots (not shown) that mate with horizontal slots in the support bracket,
allowing adjustments in height (up/down), depth (front/back), and tilt (0–10°).
Secured with stainless steel bolts and nuts.
Secures the latch in position. It does not carry weight but locks the tile’s placement.
Adjustable for a plumb and parallel tile mounting surface, compensating
for an uneven or non-plumb concrete block wall. It features vertical slots (not shown)
that mate with horizontal slots in the support bracket, allowing adjustments
Secured with stainless steel bolts and nuts.
Enables adjustment and locking of the levelling bracket.
Transfers tile weight onto the vertical support rails.
Adjusts and secures the levelling bracket, locking tile placement.
Used for assembling, adjusting, and securing metal components.
A U-shaped metal tie, epoxied to the back of the tile, which mates with a latch.
An adjustable component allowing tile tilting (side-to-side or front-to-back)
for fine alignment with adjacent tiles.
An aluminum angle component that mates with an angled surface
on the tile’s backside, transferring weight to the horizontal support rail.
Allows for height (up/down) and lateral (side-to-side) tile adjustments
3/8” dia. x 2” anchors secure the vertical support rails to a concrete block substrate.
Tile mounted plumb to the ground
